10. A teammate asks why you chose type = map(object({...})) instead of separate string variables for a structured environment 
    configuration. What is the most accurate explanation?
    Terraform's type system includes both primitive types (string, number, bool) and complex types, which are further divided into 
    collection types (list, map, set) and structural types (object, tuple). Complex types allow you to define variables that hold 
    multiple related values in a single, organized structure. Structural types like object also provide built-in validation — 
    Terraform will check that every required attribute is present and matches the declared type during the planning phase, catching
    configuration errors early.

