28. Your Terraform configuration includes variable validation, a precondition on a resource, a postcondition on the same resource, and a check block. In what order does 
Terraform evaluate these validations during a terraform apply?
Variable validation > precondition > postcondition > check
Terraform evaluates validations at specific points in its workflow. Variable validation runs first during the planning phase, before Terraform even contacts providers. 
Precondition blocks evaluate after the plan is generated but before resources are created. Postcondition blocks run after Terraform creates or updates resources. 
Finally, check blocks execute as the last step after all other operations complete, providing monitoring without blocking deployment. This layered approach creates defensive
validation at each stage of infrastructure provisioning.

29. A colleague suggests using var.bucket_name inside the backend block to make it dynamic. Will this work?
