34. When an HCP Terraform workspace is set to remote execution mode, where does terraform plan execute?
HCP Terraform supports two primary execution modes: remote and local. In remote execution mode (the default), Terraform runs — including plan and apply — execute on HCP 
Terraform's own managed, disposable virtual machines. Your local CLI streams the output back to your terminal, but the actual work happens remotely. This enables features
like Sentinel policy enforcement, cost estimation, and run notifications that depend on remote execution.

35. A production database managed by Terraform needs to be handed off to another team's Terraform configuration. What happens when you use a removed block with
lifecycle { destroy = false }?
The removed block with destroy = false removes a resource from Terraform's state file without touching the actual infrastructure. The database continues to run in your 
cloud provider exactly as it was, but Terraform no longer tracks or manages it. This is the correct approach when handing off resources between teams or configurations.
The other team can then use an import block to bring the existing database under their Terraform management. If destroy were set to true (or omitted, since true is the default),
Terraform would destroy the database when removing it from state.

