48. Your configuration uses a registry module with version = "~> 2.0" and your lock file contains version 2.3.0. A new version 2.5.0 is published. What happens when a team member
runs terraform init?
Terraform continues using version 2.3.0 from the lock file.
The dependency lock file (.terraform.lock.hcl) ensures consistent module and provider versions across team members and environments. When the lock file exists and contains
a specific version, Terraform will continue using that locked version even if newer versions are available that match the version constraint. To upgrade to 2.5.0, someone 
must explicitly run terraform init -upgrade, which updates the lock file to the newest version matching the constraint. Then, when other team members pull the updated lock 
file and run terraform init, they'll all get version 2.5.0.

