50. During the Terraform workflow, when does Terraform show you what changes will be made before actually modifying your infrastructure?
The Plan stage is specifically designed for this purpose. Terraform generates an execution plan describing the infrastructure it will create, update, or destroy based
on existing infrastructure and your configuration. It then prompts you for approval before the Apply stage modifies anything. This preview capability is a key feature
for safely managing infrastructure changes.

51. What is the correct syntax for sourcing a module from the Terraform Registry?
The correct syntax for sourcing a module from the Terraform Registry is source = "NAMESPACE/NAME/PROVIDER". Terraform automatically knows to look in the public
Terraform Registry when you use this three-part naming convention. You don't need to include the full registry URL — that's implied by the shorthand syntax. 
The namespace comes first (the organization or user who published the module), then the module name, then the provider.


















